Kate Moss is proving she's as fierce as ever as she proudly poses naked at the age of 43. 
Absolutely nothing will slow the supermodel down and she looks as unbelievably stunning as ever. 
The modelling legend is no stranger to posing naked for the camera and looks magnificent in her latest pics for W magazine . 
She was one of five influential women asked to pose for this month's magazine cover, but it's her solo images that will surely grab the most attention. Read More Kate looks amazing as she poses naked (Photo: Mert Alas & Marcus Piggott) Kate was discovered by a modelling agent when she was just 14 (Photo: Zebra One Gallery) 
In the stunning images, Kate stands completely nude with her head held high. 
A jacket hanging off her arms slightly conceals her modesty, as does the moody lighting. 
A light shining from behind casts a shadow over Kate, while accentuating her breasts and toned physique. 
She looks as amazing as many of us can only ever dream of looking. Jessica Chastain also took part in a photo shoot (Photo: Mert Alas & Marcus Piggott) Taraji P Henson is on the magazine cover too (Photo: Mert Alas & Marcus Piggott) 
Moss first posed naked at the age of 16, with the images catapulting her to worldwide fame. 
They were shot by late British photographer Corinne Day and published in The Face magazine in 1990. 
Speaking to W about the photoshoot, she said: "I was only 16. And I was so nervous. I’m still nervous! We shot the story with Corinne for a month. And then [the art director] Fabien Baron saw the story and showed it to Elizabeth Tilberis at Harper’s Bazaar, who put me with [the photographer] Patrick Demarchelier, and I was on the cover of the Christmas issue. And then Patrick was shooting Calvin Klein. And I met Calvin - and that was when everything changed." Donatella Versace features in W too (Photo: Mert Alas & Marcus Piggott) Jennifer Lopez also posed for the camera (Photo: Mert Alas & Marcus Piggott) 
Kate was first discovered at the age of 14 at a New York airport, and has admitted that her own mother didn't believe that a modelling agent wanted to sign her daughter, as she didn't think she was that "photogenic". 
The blonde beauty said: "My mum said, ‘I don’t think you’re that photogenic!’  
"From the beginning, photographers always got me to take my clothes off, even though I don’t like my body at all. I just had to get comfortable with being naked." This month's W Magazine (Photo: Mert Alas & Marcus Piggott) 
Well Kate, we think you're as devastatingly beautiful today as you've ever been. 
You go, girl! 
Kate is on the cover of W alongside Jennifer Lopez, Taraji P. Henson, Donatella Versace and Jessica Chastain. Like us on Facebook
